724566f.title: Manhattan: West Street - Carlisle Street
724566f.text:
West Street, east side, north from but not including Carlisle, to but not including Liberty Streets. Prominent building shown is
the West Street Building, No. 87-93. o
July 28. 1923.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

724563f-c.title: Manhattan: West Street - Albany Street
724563f-c.text:
(1)
Viest Street, east side, from Albany to Carlisle Streets. Also shown is Albany Street, south side, east from Vest, to and including Greeuwi:h
Streets.
August 15, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, at a later date, showing the area after practically all the houses which formerly stood there, were rased. Albany Street is seen on
the left.
April 17, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same, from a different angle. Note the 5-story house at the N.E. corner of Carlisle Street in process of being demolished. Also shown (background) is the Singer Building, at the N.W. corner of Broadway and
Liberty Street.
April 17, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
